data.description: Welcome home to this Beautiful stately home in the Historical District of Texarkana! The spacious home has charm of the past as well as some modern conveniences. Large old trees give great shade to the front yard. Sprinkler system keeps the grass and landscaping looking pretty. The landscaping and wood privacy fence has been added to enhance the curb appeal. The entry way invites you in with marble flooring that extends into the kitchen and breakfast area. The kitchen cabinets have just been freshly painted! They are Beautiful! Seller has added a new dishwasher.  Laundry room area has been freshly painted as well! Preparing meals in this Kitchen would be enjoyable and Great for entertaining your guests. Wet bar is conveniently located between the kitchen and living area. The cigar room/den area has the walls of wood that lend charm to days of the past. There are 2 living areas with fireplaces to keep you warm and cozy on those chilly nights. Bedrooms with original hardwood are nicely sized with large closets with built ins. Great size primary suite to retreat to after a long day, with large closets and built ins. Bath has new tiled shower and vanity. Balcony offers space to relax and enjoy the beautiful surroundings.  Garage has room for 2 cars and a work space area. The patio area is private overlooking large backyard for entertaining or children. Home is located just minutes from I-30, Stateline Ave. and Downtown for Restaurants.
